messages.message:
Hey Germany,
Anschluss is an essential aspect of the game for the two of us. I hope we can work together here in the early years. What are your thoughts on the Russian?

Hey Italy,
I hope to work with you and to prevent the RT that's so common. Any interest in a Key Lepanto?

Hey Russia,
Would you like to bounce Galicia?
No thoughts yet. Gonna have to see how this opening goes. Agree, though! Us middle board players gotta stick together!
Hi Austria! While we aren't neighbors now, I hope we can work together in the future.

Hey Turkey,
I know that Austria and Turkey usually get off to a rough start, but if we get a good first year together we can do some really nice work together. What are your thoughts on Russia and Italy?

Hey France,
I think that's always a good way to start!
We should keep a mutual eye on the Italian. Have you heard from him yet?
Russia?

Hey England,
A pink and red map is a pretty neat board. I hope you're open to that.
What are your thoughts on the Russian?
Not yet, I've messaged him but heard nothing back!
My thoughts exactly!
Same
What are your thoughts on Italy? I haven't heard back from them yet.
Italy?
I haven't heard from him either
Hopefully he gets around to messaging us all soon.
Yea...it's pretty poor form for a live game to not even message his neighbors
Are you thinking of a WT or an EF?

He's been on though...which is good.
Any ideas on England and France?
I'm not sure what's going on. It looks like I'm possibly going to open against England. If Italy goes after me, would you be interested in joining me against him?
Well let's cross our fingers for the best!
I certainly like the idea of a WT but England seems unresponsive
What are your thoughts on Sweden?

I like France and hate England :)

Haven't heard a word from either yet.
If Italy comes after you, I will certainly jump on the bandwagon. It's Austria's best friend on the board
If you plan to go after England, have you thought of a Sealion?
Great to hear!

Yea, I think France is open to a Sealion against England since he hasn't responded either.
What about Sweden?
That is the current plan

A Sealion and then after that...Italy?
I think it's a solid option. Italy often overplays his hand early.
The potential of a strong English Navy is certainly not something I want to deal with
Don't have a strong opinion yet on Sweden. Depends on opening moves :)
I'll back you up on that. You don't want Italy coming at you and you don't want a strong England
Fair enough!
As Austria, I'm always encouraged to see a German Sweden
That's certainly the plan. Hopefully we're off to a good start

Absolutely!
I hope to see your fleet in the Channel for sure
Any word from Italy on your end?
Gonna be sure to do what I can. Would appreciate not moving against Italy right off the bat, in exchange :)
Turkey?
I won't. Austria against Italy is suicide.
Nope, nothing
If you can get Russia to send Moscow north, that would be great. You don't want a strong Russia either
Agreed. Austria falling too fast is suicide for Germany.
Or a dead Austria and you'll face a Juggernaut

messages.message: Well, if you wanted to move to Tyrolia, I think I might be able to get you into Munich this fall
Why won't you respond?
Alright, well. I'm really sorry to have had to build in Trieste. But please, we can still work together if you just send me one message.
I'll think about it. It's probably a bit early for me to be making enemies with Germany.
I'm also not sure that Italy won't just move into Tyrolia. I'll have to make sure.
Oh, that's a clever move you have there. You've got a free convoy right into Edinburgh.

I'm moving into Tyrolia this turn.
You may have some trouble with France. I'll help you out as much as I can.
Well, he should have seen it coming
If you had moved into the North Sea, you wouldn't be in this position.
Thanks for the heads up
I understand that, but Germany is getting way too powerful, so if you aren't going to help me slow him down, he will eventually get the upper hand against me and you'll be left alone
I'll move into Tyrolia this turn. I think you can probably take Munich this turn if you try.
I hope so! I'm actually going to try for Holland with Ruhr, and I'll support Tyrolia into Munich in the fall
France is trying to convince me to attack you. I'm going to wait until next turn, when I get another build to really finish off Russia and Turkey.
Sounds good to me
I can try to feed you info about what he's doing this turn.
I won't be much use to you as an ally if you do attack me
That'd be appreciated

Alright. I think that's a good plan.
You should move Brest to the MAO, and try to slip into North Sea this turn.
